    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#paci2011"/>, p. <citedRange>268</citedRange> and fig. 13, n. 5</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>61.1555.A.3</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>115300</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#gasparini-rosamilia2016"/>, pp. <citedRange>190-195</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>66.2322</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ης"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">ευς</seg></name></persName> 
                    <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Γλαῦκος">Γλαύκ<supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ès fils de Glaukos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>es son of Glaucos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>es figlio di Glaukos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>One of the numerous instances of a rock-cut <foreign rend="italic">eschara</foreign>, probably used for personal offerings of the man who cut his name in front of the compartment(s),
                   letting know that he is its owner or user, whereas the honoured deity remains unknown.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
